The paper deals with the performance evaluation of wireless networks with multi-antenna linear MMSE receivers, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the impact of spatial node distributions on network performance, which falls under the category of spatial information (cs.SI). The use of MMSE receivers is a technique related to signal processing (cs.SP) and the paper also discusses the convergence of the SIR, which is a topic related to probability and statistics (cs.PF).
